description.narrative: The objective of the Project is to assist the Borrower to reduce poverty and to support mechanisms for the promotion of a peaceful and safe environment in the conflict-affected areas in the ARMM Region and in particular to: (a) improve access to social and economic infrastructure and livelihood opportunities; (b) strengthen social cohesion and partnerships between and within targeted communities; and (c) improve local governance and institutional capacities for implementation in the ARMM Region, with a focus on improved participation, transparency and accountability in the allocation and management of public resources by the participating communities, local government units and ARMM Regional Government.

condition.narrative: ARMM Regional Government and the Fund shall enter into a Memorandum of Agreement
Fund shall adopt Policies/Guidelines for operations and management and shall not amend, delete, suspend, abrogate or waive anyprovision thereof, without the approval of the Bank
Fund shall adopt and thereafter apply in the implementation of the Project, an Operations Manual satisfactory to the Bank
Fund shall appoint by June 30, 2003 an internal auditor within CFMO under Terms of Reference satisfactory to the Bank
Fund shall by October 1 of each year adopt an annual work plan including training and technical assistance program, and budget andfurnish plan to the Bank for its review and comments.
Fund shall carry on its operations and conduct its affairs with due diligence and efficiency, in accordance with appropriateprocedures
Fund shall comply with the accounting, financial reporting and auditing procedures set forth in the Operations Manual
Fund shall contract an independent auditor to prepare an annual management and operation audit of the Project and provide the Bankwith said audits not later than August 30 of each Fiscal Year
Fund shall ensure that Beneficiary for sub-projects comply with the provisions for the procurement of goods, works and consultantsservices set forth in Section 3.02 and Schedule 4 to Loan Agreement
Fund shall ensure that sub-project proposals prepare a Land Acquisition & RAP, if required, and undertake compensation andmitigation measures in accordance with the Resettlement Policy Framework
Fund shall ensure that sub-project proposals undertake environmental impact analysis and mitigation measures, if required, basedonthe Environmental Framework
Fund shall ensure that the proposals involving Indigenous Peoples incorporates an IPDP for informed participation of IPs inaccordance with the IP Framework
Fund shall enter into sub-project MOA with relevant Beneficiary in regard to each sub-project approved for financing. No grantfunds will be provided without a MOA.
Fund shall have the work plan approved by its Board of Directors by December of each year, and thereafter carry out such work plan
Fund shall maintain policies and procedures adequate to enable it to monitor and evaluate on an ongoing basis, in accordance withthe indicators set forth in Schedule 7 to this Agreement
Fund shall prepare and furnish to the Bank: (i) by January 31 and July 31 of each year, a semi-annual report; and (ii) on or aboutAugust 31, 2005, a mid-term report
Fund shall review MTR report with Borrower and Bank, by Sept 30, 2005, or such later date as the Bank shall request, and, take allmeasures to ensure the efficient completion of the Project
No later than 6 months after effectiveness, the PMO shall carry out an assessment of the risks to Project implementation inMaguindanao and act on recommendations acceptable to the Bank.
The PMO shall, by Jan 31, 2011, appoint an independent third party to conduct the spot checks referred to in Section I A 3.
The PMO shall, not later than Jan 31 and July 31 in each year, commencing July 31, 2011 and until July 31, 2013, carry out spotchecks to verify Beneficiaries meet the eligibility criteria
